cs.GR, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with learning structures of 3D shapes, which is a fundamental problem in computer graphics and geometry processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GR (Computer Graphics). The paper also involves the use of local features and point integration module, which are common techniques in computer vision and machine learning. Hence, it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper proposes an unsupervised method for learning a new structural representation, which falls under the category of unsupervised learning, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. Finally, the paper uses the chamfer distance as a reconstruction loss, which is a common technique in neural networks and optimization, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible category.
